overview: The user's intent was to enhance a sleep questionnaire application by
  adding persistent storage for responses and providing an administrative
  interface for data access. The approach involved integrating a PostgreSQL
  database (NeonDB) via Prisma, designing a a QuestionnaireResponse schema to
  store raw data and denormalized demographics, and developing API endpoints for
  data submission and retrieval. A key decision was to implement a simple
  password-based authentication system using HTTP-only cookies for the admin
  dashboard, which includes a login page and a table view with CSV export
  functionality. The questionnaire form was updated to submit data to the new
  backend. The implementation successfully covered all specified requirements,
  setting up a robust data management and access system for the application.
